t you’re unconditionally dispatching an action during render, so your component enters a loop: render, dispatch (which causes a render), render, dispatch (which causes a render), and so on. Very often, this is caused by a mistake in specifying an event handler:
// 🚩 Wrong: calls the handler during render
return <button onClick={handleClick()}>Click me</button>
// ✅ Correct: passes down the event handler
return <button onClick={handleClick}>Click me</button>
